  "blocker": "PR #488 added an explicit SGLang /flush_cache call before the post-live-check model-quality canary. The Databricks run used the fresh f95d4f0 wheel on g6.8xlarge, generated the Qwen-chat handoff, hydrated all expected Cachet-backed SGLang pages, and preserved the full 175-token cache-arm hit. The flush returned HTTP 200 and the model-quality canary then produced cachet-green with zero cached tokens, clearing the previous canary-contamination blocker. The run is still not a publishable SGLang benchmark because both baseline and cache-arm live quality returned repeated filler text instead of the expected NIAH answer."
